  "prompt": "What is kale called in Hindi or Marathi?",
  "response": "In Hindi, kale is called \"\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0915 \u0917\u094b\u092d\u0940\" (paalak gobhi) or \"\u0915\u093e\u0932\u0940 \u0917\u094b\u092d\u0940\" (kali gobhi), while in Marathi, it is referred to as \"\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0915\" (paalak). However, it's important to note that \"\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0915\" generally means spinach in both Hindi and Marathi, so if you specifically want to refer to the kale variety, you might describe it as a type of gobhi or cabbage to distinguish it from regular spinach.",
